<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>
Essential Presentation library has support for creating animation in a PowerPoint slide.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates how to add different animation effect for shapes.</Paragraph>
<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<Paragraph>The below animation effects are supported as equivalent to Microsoft PowerPoint:</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Entrance</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Emphasis</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Exit</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Motion paths</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph>The below animation options are supported as equivalent to Microsoft PowerPoint:</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Effect options</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Add multiple animations</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Trigger</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Animation timing</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
